<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Python Programming</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f2f2f2;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        header {
            background-color: #0073e6;
            color: #fff;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 24px;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #fff;
            border-radius: 5px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        p {
            font-size: 16px;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .btn {
            display: inline-block;
            background-color: #0073e6;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }

        .btn:hover {
            background-color: #005bac;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Welcome to Python Programming</h1>
    </header>
    <div class="container">
        <h2>What is Python?</h2>
        <p>Python is a versatile and widely-used programming language known for its simplicity and readability. It is a great choice for beginners and experienced developers alike. Python is used in various fields, including web development, data science, artificial intelligence, and more.</p>

        <h2>Getting Started with Python</h2>
        <p>If you're new to Python, you can start learning by visiting the official Python website and checking out the <a href="https://www.python.org/about/gettingstarted/" class="btn">Getting Started</a> section. There, you'll find resources and tutorials to help you begin your Python journey.</p>

        <h2>Python Resources</h2>
        <p>Explore the world of Python programming by using online tutorials, books, and courses. Here are a few recommended resources:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="https://docs.python.org/3/" class="btn">Python Official Documentation</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.learnpython.org/" class="btn">LearnPython.org</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://realpython.com/" class="btn">Real Python</a></li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
